76561197971907582,Recommended,211900,543514,"Posted: 22 February, 2013",all,ThatWhichThinks,"This game is about as old-school as you can get without whipping out a floppy disk.  Its layout, graphics, and gameplay could probably have all been programmed with technology available in the late 80's.  But, even with all of that, this is one of the most interesting strategy games I have ever played.  The world and mythos are unique (even though the maps themselves are randomly generated), the magical powers of each leader are distinct and interesting (each of the 17 or so races has completely different game mechanics), and the wide range of creatures and events make this game compelling far beyond what screenshots would suggest. If you like grand strategy or were a fan of the old Lords of Magic, give this a try."
