76561198140435102,Recommended,211900,31774961,Posted: 15 May,all,savvym,"This is ridiculous game. I had to figure out the controls after 30 minutes of playing because otherwise I would be lost. After I have learned to control my units, I have beaten up my 2 enemies which were 2 difficulty. There are maybe 10 difficulties. I tried the easy first to see what it does.You will get a leader and a town who can lead some units. In the beginning you have one farm or resource which gives you +1 gold. Accumulated gold is used for units. There are some special units offers during some months. Each turn is one month. The world changes depending on the seasons.During gameplay I got one special leader who was useful mage.Battles are simulations on screen, each unit takes its turn, you can speed it up or skip the battle.There are running creatures in the world which are neutral and can attack you as well as enemies.You can see by right-clicking on them what stats they have. If you remember old M&M right-clicking on opponents, it also stops the game during combat, but you can see all their abilities, buffs and damage.There are some hidden units and you uncover the world from fog of war.By losing your leader or killing the enemy leader, you eliminate the faction. Units, if not leaders, can not move on their own. They must be transfered to leaders. Otherwise they only defend current tile.Leaders can move from 1 to 3 tiles, maybe more...So far I like the game, it is a little challenging, you must accumulate enough units to defeat some enemies, but hard to say if it is challenging on higher difficulties as I only played the easy.Yeah, and graphics are not so good as you can see, units do a little animation and it has some music in background, sounds in battle are ridiculous. Overally, game is well-focused on tactics."
